data.enText: to make sb unable to think clearly or understand sth

data.chText: 他们对发生的事所作的陈述自相矛盾，使我迷惑不解。
data.enText: They confused me with conflicting accounts of what happened.
to think wrongly that sb/sth is sb/sth else

data.chText: 人们常常把我和我的孪生妹妹搞错。
data.enText: People often confuse me and my twin sister.

data.chText: 注意不要把数量与质量混淆了。
data.enText: Be careful not to confuse quantity with quality.
to make a subject more difficult to understand

data.chText: 他的评论只是把问题弄得更加复杂。
data.enText: His comments only served to confuse the issue further.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 共同 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 流到一起 → 使混乱

ex.chText: 令他不解的是，为什么那部电影如此受欢迎。
ex.enText: What puzzles him is why that movie is so popular.

ex.chText: 那个问题继续困扰着科学家们。
ex.enText: That question continues to puzzle scientists.

synonyms.bx: 指无法理解某事而感到有些困扰。

ex.chText: 完形填空测验难倒了她班上的很多学生。
ex.enText: The cloze test baffled many students in her class.

ex.chText: 他完全被她怪异的举动搞糊涂了。
ex.enText: He was completely baffled by her strange behaviour.

synonyms.bx: 指完全不能理解或解释问题、行为等。

ex.chText: 他的话把她给弄糊涂了。
ex.enText: She was bewildered by his remarks.

ex.chText: 那个年轻人给搞糊涂了，不知道该相信谁。
ex.enText: That young man was bewildered as to whom to believe.

synonyms.bx: 多指不知所措、无法清楚地思考，通常用被动语态。

ex.chText: 所附的详细使用指南使我更加迷惑。
ex.enText: The detailed instructions for use only served to confuse me further.

ex.chText: 其中一些数字把他给弄糊涂了。
ex.enText: Some of the figures confused him.

synonyms.bx: 词义同 bewilder，但程度略轻。

example: you are confusing me with the other candidate
I mistook her for the secretary

tr: cause to be unable to think clearly
example: These questions confuse even the experts
This question befuddled even the teacher
She jumbles the words when she is supposed to write a sentence
The constant attention of the young man confused her

value.def: If you confuse two things, you get them mixed up, so that you think one of them is the other one.

example.ex: Great care is taken to avoid confusing the two types of projects...
example.tran: 大家非常谨慎，以免把这两类项目弄混。

example.ex: I can't see how anyone could confuse you with another!
example.tran: 我不明白怎么会有人把你和另外一个人搞混！

example.ex: Use different colours of felt pen on your sketch to avoid confusion.
example.tran: 用不同颜色的毡头笔画草图，以免搞混。

value.def: To confuse someone means to make it difficult for them to know exactly what is happening or what to do.

example.ex: German politics surprised and confused  him.
example.tran: 德国政治既令他惊讶，又让他困惑不解。

value.def: To confuse a situation means to make it complicated or difficult to understand.

example.ex: To further confuse the issue, there is an enormous variation in the amount of sleep people feel happy with.
example.tran: 使问题进一步复杂化的是，每个人需要的睡眠时间千差万别。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to pour, to melt 流, 泻；融化
rootsaffixes.title: fus

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 流到一起 → 使混乱
dif 分开 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 分流 → 散播
ef 出 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 流出；吐露
ef 出 + fus 流，泻；融化 + ive …的 →〔感情〕流出的 → 溢出的
in 进入 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 流进去 → 注入
pro 向前 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 不断向前涌出的 → 丰富的
re 相反 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 向回流 → 拒绝
re 反 + fut〔= fus〕流，泻；融化 + e → 反流 → 反驳
suf 下 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 在下面流〔得到处都是〕→ 充满
trans 横过 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e →〔让血〕穿过 → 输血
